If Census API calls fail for 2020, the code silently substitutes 2021 state populations as 2020 denominators when computing 2020 crude mortality rates. This can bias 2020 rates (especially for fast-growing/declining states) and can differentially affect treated vs control if adoption correlates with population growth patterns. The manuscript emphasizes COVID-era volatility and robustness, but this denominator substitution is not described as a sensitivity check and may affect 2020 (the first treatment year) most.: if (is.null(pop_data[["2020"]]) && !is.null(pop_data[["2021"]])) {
  cat("  Using 2021 population as proxy for 2020\n")
  pop_data[["2020"]] <- pop_data[["2021"]] %>% mutate(year = 2020L)
}
